  "prompt": "What is the food you can eat every day for breakfast, lunch and dinner?",
  "response": "While it's generally best to have a varied diet to ensure you're getting a wide range of nutrients, there are a few foods that are versatile, nutritious, and sustainable to eat daily for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Here are some examples:\n\n1. **Eggs**  \n   - Breakfast: Scrambled, boiled, or as an omelet.  \n   - Lunch: In a salad or as a sandwich filling.  \n   - Dinner: In a stir-fry or as part of a frittata.  \n\n2. **Oats**  \n   - Breakfast: Oatmeal with fruits and nuts.  \n   - Lunch: Overnight oats with yogurt and seeds.  \n   - Dinner: Savory oats with vegetables and cheese.  \n\n3. **Rice**  \n   - Breakfast: Rice porridge (congee) with eggs or vegetables.  \n   - Lunch: Fried rice with veggies and protein.  \n   - Dinner: Steamed rice with curry or stir-fried dishes.  \n\n4. **Quinoa**  \n   - Breakfast: Quinoa porridge with almond milk and berries.  \n   - Lunch: Quinoa salad with roasted vegetables.  \n   - Dinner: Quinoa stir-fry with tofu or chicken.  \n\n5. **Avocado**  \n   - Breakfast: On toast with eggs.  \n   - Lunch: In a salad or wrap.  \n   - Dinner: As a topping for bowls or stuffed with protein.  \n\n6. **Chicken**  \n   - Breakfast: Shredded chicken in a breakfast burrito.  \n   - Lunch: Grilled chicken salad or sandwich.  \n   - Dinner: Roasted or pan-seared chicken with sides.  \n\n7. **Potatoes**  \n   - Breakfast: Hash browns or breakfast potatoes.  \n   - Lunch: Baked potato with toppings.  \n   - Dinner: Mashed, roasted, or as fries.  \n\n8. **Beans or Lentils**  \n   - Breakfast: In a breakfast burrito or savory pancake.  \n   - Lunch: Bean salad or lentil soup.  \n   - Dinner: Curried lentils or bean stew.  \n\n9. **Greek Yogurt**  \n   - Breakfast: With granola and fruit.  \n   - Lunch: As a dip or in a smoothie.  \n   - Dinner: In sauces or as a dessert with honey.  \n\n10. **Whole Grain Bread**  \n    - Breakfast: Toast with spreads or as part of avocado toast.  \n    - Lunch: Sandwich with veggies and protein.  \n    - Dinner: As a side with soup or stew.  \n\nWhile these foods are nutritious, it's important to include a variety of fruits, vegetables, proteins, and healthy fats in your diet to meet all your nutritional needs. Eating the same thing every day can lead to nutrient deficiencies or boredom with your meals.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
